PIVOT BUILDER CLOUD - SIMPLE HOW TO USE GUIDE
=============================================

This guide is for the single-workbook Office Script version.


PART 1 - HOW TO RUN IT
======================

1. Open the workbook in Excel for Web.

2. Go to the Automate tab.

3. Run the Pivot Builder script.

4. First run:
   - The script creates a sheet named:
     PivotBuilder_Setup
   - It also creates the starter layout for you.

5. Go to PivotBuilder_Setup.

6. Fill in row 9 (or the next empty setup row).

7. Make sure cell B4 says:
   Build pivots

8. Run the script again.

9. The script will:
   - build PivotTables, or
   - append/update raw columns if Input Sheet = Output Sheet

10. If Excel stops because of time limit:
   - run the same script again
   - it will continue from where it stopped


PART 2 - NORMAL USER FLOW
=========================

1. Run the script once.
2. Setup sheet appears.
3. Fill in one or more setup rows.
4. Run the script again.
5. Check the result sheets.
6. Edit setup if needed.
7. Run again.


PART 3 - MAIN SETUP COLUMNS
===========================

Each setup row creates one output.

Input Sheet
-----------
Source sheet to read from.

You can also use:
{Month}

Example:
Call {Month}


Template
--------
Used to group setups.

Examples:
1/KPI
1/Call Result
2/PV

Template selection supports:
- exact match
- parent group match
- All
- All Templates


Pivot Name
----------
The name of this pivot block.


Output Sheet
------------
The sheet where the result goes.


Rows
----
The row fields for the pivot.

Normal example:
Agent,Campaign Name

Custom row rule example:
Morning: Time Band=Morning & Team=Call


Row Names
---------
Optional display names matching the Rows items in order.

Example:
Rows      = Agent,Campaign Name
Row Names = Owner,Campaign


Calculated Columns
------------------
Extra columns/formulas added after the pivot is built.

If Input Sheet = Output Sheet, Calculated Columns are appended to the raw data sheet instead of building a pivot.


Values To Count/Sum
-------------------
Fields to summarize.

Behavior:
- numeric field -> Sum
- text field -> Count

Examples:
Premium
Policy No.
Premium,Policy No.


Filters
-------
Filter fields or preselected filter values.


Conditions
----------
Condition-based pivot categories/columns built from source data.


Next Pivot Right
----------------
Yes = try placing the next pivot to the right
No/blank = place the next pivot below


Notes
-----
For your own comments only.


